  "prompt": "How does Usain Bolt train?",
  "response": "Usain Bolt's training regime includes a combination of various elements designed to improve his speed, strength, and overall athletic performance. Although specific details of his workouts can vary, key components generally include:\n\n1. **Strength Training**:\n   - Weightlifting exercises to build muscle power, focusing on the legs, core, and upper body.\n   - Plyometric exercises like jumping and bounding to enhance explosive strength.\n\n2. **Speed Work**:\n   - Sprint drills and practice runs to fine-tune his running technique and improve speed.\n   - Interval training involving high-intensity sprints followed by rest periods to increase his sprinting endurance.\n\n3. **Endurance and Cardiovascular Training**:\n   - Endurance runs and tempo work to improve cardiovascular fitness and overall stamina.\n\n4. **Flexibility and Mobility**:\n   - Stretching routines and flexibility exercises to maintain range of motion and prevent injuries.\n   - Dynamic stretches and drills to keep his muscles loose and responsive.\n\n5. **Technical Drills**:\n   - Starts and acceleration drills focusing on his technique out of the blocks.\n   - Form drills to perfect his running posture, stride length, and arm movement.\n\n6. **Recovery**:\n   - Adequate rest and recovery, including sleep and active recovery methods.\n   - Physiotherapy sessions, massages, and sometimes using ice baths for muscle recovery.\n\n7. **Nutrition**:\n   - A balanced diet tailored to his energy needs, including carbs, proteins, fats, vitamins, and minerals to support training and recovery.\n   - Hydration is crucial, with a focus on maintaining electrolyte balance.\n\nBolt has worked closely with his coaches, notably Glenn Mills, to customize his training plan based on his specific needs and goals at different stages of his career. His commitment to training, combined with his natural talent, has helped him become one of the greatest sprinters in history.",
